title: Vaquero Breakfast Returns for 3rd Edition at Far West San Antonio | KSAB Tejano 99.9
text:
If you love rodeo, music, and tacos, you won’t want to miss the 3rd annual Vaquero Breakfast at Far West San Antonio on Friday, January 26, 2024, at 7:00 a.m. This event is presented by Lopez Entertainment and features some of the best Tejano and Country music artists in Texas.
The Vaquero Breakfast is a tradition that honors the cowboys and cowgirls who participate in the rodeo. It’s also a way to kick off the rodeo season in San Antonio with a bang. You can enjoy a free breakfast of delicious tacos while listening to live performances from Los Desperadoz , Jase Martin , Jay Martinez & The Boys , Jukebox Preachers featuring Art Tigerina , El Dorado Band , JJ & PJ Villarreal , Mario Moreno , Jordan Guana , Justin Gallegos , and Cheyenne Saenz .
The event will also have an indoor vendor market where you can shop for unique items and support local businesses. The best part is that the entry is free and so is the breakfast, while supplies last.
Far West San Antonio is located at 2502 Pleasanton Road. a spacious venue that can accommodate large crowds and has plenty of parking. If you want to upgrade your experience, you can reserve a VIP table by calling 210-777-7839.
The Vaquero Breakfast is a fun and family-friendly event that celebrates the culture and heritage of San Antonio. Don’t miss this opportunity to enjoy some great music, food, and entertainment.
Follow Tejano Nation on Facebook , X (formerly Twitter), and Instagram , and subscribe to our YouTube channel to keep up with everything Tejano. Listen to new Tejano music first with our Spotify playlists and iHeartRadio podcast.
